    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The Message Batches API provides a 50% discount on all token costs in exchange for asynchronous, non-guaranteed turnaround up to 24 hours. For workloads that tolerate latency \u2014 nightly analytics, evaluation pipelines, bulk content processing \u2014 this is the cheapest way to use Claude at scale. The API is purpose-built for high-volume, offline workloads that would otherwise consume real-time rate limit quota."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Message Batches API flow and cost comparison"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When to Use Batch Processing"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Batch processing is the right choice when:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Latency tolerance",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Results are not needed for minutes or hours \u2014 nightly reports, daily pipelines, periodic evaluations."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "High volume",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Thousands of similar requests that would saturate real-time rate limits."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Cost sensitivity",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": The 50% discount is material to your budget."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Avoiding rate limit pressure",
                    "marks": [
                      {
                        "type": "bold"
                      }
                    ]
                  },
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": ": Batch requests use a separate low-priority queue and do not count against your real-time tokens-per-minute limits."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Do not use batch processing for user-facing features, real-time chat, latency-sensitive inference, or any workflow where the user is waiting for a response."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Submitting a Batch"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Each batch contains a list of request objects, each with a unique "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "custom_id",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and a standard messages API payload:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import anthropic\n\nclient = anthropic.Anthropic()\n\n# Build a batch of document summarization requests\ndocuments = [\n    {\"id\": \"doc_001\", \"text\": \"Annual report text for Acme Corp...\"},\n    {\"id\": \"doc_002\", \"text\": \"Annual report text for Globex Corp...\"},\n    # ... up to 10,000 items per batch\n]\n\nbatch = client.messages.batches.create(\n    requests=[\n        {\n            \"custom_id\": doc[\"id\"],\n            \"params\": {\n                \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n                \"max_tokens\": 512,\n                \"messages\": [\n                    {\n                        \"role\": \"user\",\n                        \"content\": f\"Summarize this annual report in 3 bullet points:\\n\\n{doc['text']}\",\n                    }\n                ],\n            },\n        }\n        for doc in documents\n    ]\n)\n\nprint(f\"Batch ID: {batch.id}\")\nprint(f\"Status:   {batch.processing_status}\")   # \"in_progress\"\nprint(f\"Requests: {batch.request_counts.processing}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Batch limits: ",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "bold"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Up to 10,000 requests per batch. Individual requests in the batch follow the same "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "max_tokens",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "code"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " and context limits as real-time requests. Each request is billed independently at 50% of standard input and output rates."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Polling for Completion"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Batches process asynchronously. Poll the batch status until "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "processing_status",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " is "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\"ended\"",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import time\n\ndef wait_for_batch(batch_id: str, poll_interval: int = 60) -> anthropic.types.MessageBatch:\n    \"\"\"Poll until the batch ends. Returns the completed batch object.\"\"\"\n    while True:\n        batch = client.messages.batches.retrieve(batch_id)\n        counts = batch.request_counts\n        print(\n            f\"Status: {batch.processing_status} | \"\n            f\"processing={counts.processing} \"\n            f\"succeeded={counts.succeeded} \"\n            f\"errored={counts.errored} \"\n            f\"canceled={counts.canceled}\"\n        )\n        if batch.processing_status == \"ended\":\n            return batch\n        time.sleep(poll_interval)\n\ncompleted = wait_for_batch(batch.id)\nprint(f\"Ended at: {completed.ended_at}\")\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Poll every 30\u201360 seconds for small batches. For large batches expected to take hours, 5-minute intervals are fine \u2014 polling more frequently does not speed up processing."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Retrieving Results"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Once the batch has ended, stream the results as JSONL. Results are not guaranteed to arrive in submission order; match by "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "custom_id",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ":"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "results = {}\nerrors  = {}\n\nfor result in client.messages.batches.results(batch.id):\n    if result.result.type == \"succeeded\":\n        message = result.result.message\n        results[result.custom_id] = message.content[0].text\n    elif result.result.type == \"errored\":\n        error = result.result.error\n        errors[result.custom_id] = {\n            \"type\":    error.type,\n            \"message\": error.message,\n        }\n    elif result.result.type == \"canceled\":\n        # Request was in a canceled batch\n        errors[result.custom_id] = {\"type\": \"canceled\"}\n\nprint(f\"Succeeded: {len(results)}, Errored: {len(errors)}\")\n\n# Example: retrieve the summary for doc_001\nprint(results.get(\"doc_001\"))\n"
          }
        ]
      },
