      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Handling Partial Failures"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Some requests in a batch may fail while others succeed. The batch itself reaches "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\"ended\"",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " regardless. A robust pipeline separates successes from failures, logs errors, and resubmits only the failed items:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "def process_batch_results(batch_id: str, original_requests: list[dict]) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns {custom_id: result_text} for succeeded requests.\n    Logs errored requests for resubmission.\n    \"\"\"\n    request_map = {r[\"custom_id\"]: r for r in original_requests}\n    succeeded = {}\n    to_retry  = []\n\n    for result in client.messages.batches.results(batch_id):\n        if result.result.type == \"succeeded\":\n            succeeded[result.custom_id] = result.result.message.content[0].text\n        else:\n            # Preserve original request for retry\n            if result.custom_id in request_map:\n                to_retry.append(request_map[result.custom_id])\n\n    if to_retry:\n        print(f\"Resubmitting {len(to_retry)} failed requests...\")\n        retry_batch = client.messages.batches.create(requests=to_retry)\n        retry_results = process_batch_results(\n            wait_for_batch(retry_batch.id).id, to_retry\n        )\n        succeeded.update(retry_results)\n\n    return succeeded\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cost Calculation for Batches"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Batch pricing applies a 50% reduction to both input and output token rates. The same formula as real-time applies, but with halved rates:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Approximate batch prices per 1M tokens (check anthropic.com/pricing for current rates)\nBATCH_PRICES = {\n    \"claude-haiku-4-5\":  {\"input\": 0.40,  \"output\": 2.00},   # 50% of standard\n    \"claude-sonnet-4-6\": {\"input\": 1.50,  \"output\": 7.50},\n    \"claude-opus-4-8\":   {\"input\": 7.50,  \"output\": 37.50},\n}\n\ndef estimate_batch_cost(\n    n_requests: int,\n    avg_input_tokens: int,\n    avg_output_tokens: int,\n    model: str,\n) -> float:\n    rates = BATCH_PRICES[model]\n    total_input  = n_requests * avg_input_tokens\n    total_output = n_requests * avg_output_tokens\n    return (\n        total_input  / 1_000_000 * rates[\"input\"]\n        + total_output / 1_000_000 * rates[\"output\"]\n    )\n\n# 5,000 document summaries on Sonnet\n# avg 2,000 input tokens, 400 output tokens each\ncost = estimate_batch_cost(5_000, 2_000, 400, \"claude-sonnet-4-6\")\nprint(f\"Estimated batch cost: ${cost:.2f}\")\n# = 5000 * 2000/1M * $1.50 + 5000 * 400/1M * $7.50\n# = $15.00 + $15.00 = $30.00\n# vs $60.00 real-time \u2014 saving $30.00 on this batch\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Batch Processing With Prompt Caching"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prompt caching and batch processing can be combined. Cache write (1.25\u00d7 premium) and read (0.10\u00d7 rate) charges apply within a batch, stacked on top of the 50% batch discount. Cache reads within a batch hit the same server-side cache as real-time requests:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# System prompt cached across all batch requests\nSYSTEM = [\n    {\n        \"type\": \"text\",\n        \"text\": LARGE_REFERENCE_DOCUMENT,  # 20,000 tokens\n        \"cache_control\": {\"type\": \"ephemeral\"},\n    }\n]\n\nbatch = client.messages.batches.create(\n    requests=[\n        {\n            \"custom_id\": f\"q_{i}\",\n            \"params\": {\n                \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n                \"max_tokens\": 256,\n                \"system\": SYSTEM,\n                \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": question}],\n            },\n        }\n        for i, question in enumerate(questions)\n    ]\n)\n# First request in the batch: pays 1.25\u00d7 for cache write on 20,000 tokens\n# All subsequent requests: pay 0.10\u00d7 for cache read\n# Combined with 50% batch discount: effective cache-read cost = 0.10\u00d7 * 0.50 = 0.05\u00d7 standard\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Canceling a Batch"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "You can cancel an in-progress batch. Requests already completed are billed; pending requests are canceled and not billed:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Cancel if you discover an error in the batch after submission\ncanceled = client.messages.batches.cancel(batch.id)\nprint(f\"Status after cancel request: {canceled.processing_status}\")\n# Will transition to \"ended\" with some requests in \"canceled\" state\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Large-Scale Pipeline Architecture"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For production pipelines processing millions of records, structure around daily batch windows:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nfrom datetime import datetime\n\nMAX_BATCH_SIZE = 10_000\n\nasync def nightly_pipeline(records: list[dict]) -> dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Submits records in parallel batches, waits for all to complete,\n    then aggregates results.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Split into batches of 10,000\n    batches_data = [records[i:i+MAX_BATCH_SIZE] for i in range(0, len(records), MAX_BATCH_SIZE)]\n    \n    # Submit all batches concurrently\n    batch_ids = []\n    for chunk in batches_data:\n        b = client.messages.batches.create(requests=build_requests(chunk))\n        batch_ids.append(b.id)\n        print(f\"Submitted batch {b.id} ({len(chunk)} requests)\")\n\n    # Poll all batches until complete\n    results = {}\n    pending = set(batch_ids)\n    while pending:\n        await asyncio.sleep(300)  # check every 5 minutes\n        done = set()\n        for bid in pending:\n            batch = client.messages.batches.retrieve(bid)\n            if batch.processing_status == \"ended\":\n                for result in client.messages.batches.results(bid):\n                    if result.result.type == \"succeeded\":\n                        results[result.custom_id] = result.result.message.content[0].text\n                done.add(bid)\n        pending -= done\n        print(f\"[{datetime.now():%H:%M}] {len(pending)} batches still processing\")\n\n    return results\n"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Batch vs Real-Time: Decision Guide"
          }
        ]
      },
